-e , --engine <tts-script>
Execute a user-defined script to convert a text file to audio.
A sample script, william, shows how this is done.
The script may be placed in /usr/local/bin,
and should accept parameters supplied by edway when the script is executed.
The first parameter is the name of the file to be translated,
the second is the name of the wav file that results,
and the third is the speaking rate to be used.
The script may choose to ignore the third parameter if desired.
